edu.snu.coral.runtime.common.plan.physical

Class ScheduledTaskGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.snu.coral.runtime.common.plan.physical.ScheduledTaskGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class ScheduledTaskGroup
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A ScheduledTaskGroup is a grouping of Task that belong to a stage. Executors receive units of ScheduledTaskGroups during job execution, and thus the resource type of all tasks of a ScheduledTaskGroup must be identical. A stage contains a list of IDs of TaskGroups whose length corresponds to stage/operator parallelism. This class includes all information which will be required from the executor after scheduled, including the (serialized) DAG of Tasks, the incoming/outgoing edges to/from the stage the TaskGroup belongs to, and so on.
